	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99283119222957><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=99283119222957>RE: How do I heal myself</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=99283119222957#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=30229><span id= >vadden</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>11 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jun 17th 10:26 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>There are two ways a paladin can heal themselves. The first you get as soon as you start and costs nothing. It is called Lay on Hands and is found as Lay Hands in your abilities. When you use it, it heals whatever you have targeted, whether it's yourself, a friend, or even the monster you're attacking. The amount it heals is equal to the amount of HP you have at your current level without buffs. This can be used as a "get out of jail free card" if you are close to dying in a battle. Quickly hit tab to select yourself and use it to completely refill your HP. This can be used to kill many yellow or white creatures you would otherwise not be able to kill, or you can use it to ensure a safe getaway from a losing battle. The one downside to this is that you can only use it once every 72 minutes.<br>The other way pallies heal themselves is by spells. Don't fear, you're not missing any spells yet. At level 9 you can get your first spells, bought at your local pally guild. The first set of spells includes a minor heal. They also get light, regular, and greater healing at lvls 15, 30, 49 respectively.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
