	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Now I assume your asking about the 5 practice points you gain after each new level, if so go with blacksmithing.<br>Blacksmithing is a very good trade skill to work on. Put one practice point into it, then grab all the rusty weapons you can find, (stores or monster you fight) and put one sharping stone and a rusty weapon in a forge. Hit combine and viola' use or sell your new tarnished weapon (if you get a "you made an alternate product" message keep trying).<br>If your asking about the ability points you get when you are making your character, you should try to keep them all at least 75, putting what left into Str and then Wis (thats my opinion, other will suggest something different)<br>&nbsp;<br>Ryanlynx<br>Paladin of Mith Marr<br>Xev<br><br>"Honor before Humility and all that jazz."</td></tr>
