	   <tr><td colspan=2>Getting all the parts done for Soulfire is really a matter of timing, no matter the lvl. half the quest , involves running around etc, & can be done at almost any lvl. <br>Hilt - dropped from Xicotl in MM can be done at any lvl , depending on timing. I am lvl 40 & got lucky to be there , while 9lvl 40+ guys were starting a raid. Myself & 2 guild freinds joined in to form 2 solid 40+ grps. In 2hrs we got 2 hilts , first one for the lvl 50 pally that initiated raid, & the second one for me. I have to admitt, that my contribution to killing the pulled mobs , was less than stellar. the higher lvl guys did all the damage so quick, i was barely able to get a few licks in. Anyways we cleared the castle to the front door , pulliing room by room. I felt , that if i was a lvl 25 , i would have still got my hilt, assuming the higher lvl raid grps would have let me in. The lowest lvl in on the raid was a lvl 27 druid , who did die once, ( could not take the pounding , until the melees pulled the mob off him!). Its a matter of timing & luck. When the raid party of 9 got the Hilt & a few other items, I was very appreciative that they stayed ubtill Xicotl spawned again so i could get it too.<br>Sir Lucan, Form a guild raid, OOC in EC,NF,WF & EF for peeps to join a raid. You may get lucky & find enough players willing to have some fun, hehe. With the ub=nderstanding that the testamnt off the undead Lucan defaults to you, the raid organizer. More Luck & Timing here.<br>As you can see , it does take some attainment of a lvl to surrvive in these raids, especially when the high lvl mobs , pound on ya, But with Luck & Greatr timing , It is possible.<br>My 2 cents worth, Don;t get dicouraged when you see a pally in his teens, wielding soulfire, get lucky yerself, hehe.<br>Torsk Holynite, Ad Gloriam<br>Paladin of the 40th Season<br>Gonna go Kill Lucan Tonite (Hpefully)<br>Lanys T'Vyl<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
