<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=99236253982916></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99236253982916><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=99236253982916>Fear Kiting Spectres in Oasis</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=99236253982916#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=17094><span id=Sage>Kneesmasher</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>397 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jun 12th 12:15 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.90]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>As I promised in an earlier post, after being motivated by another fellow Paladin, I have recently returned to Oasis to Fear Kite the Spectres!&nbsp;&nbsp;That little used spell called SPOOK the DEAD, which I’ve had forever collecting dust in my spell book, is now earning its keep!  Most of the Spectres on the island, that strike fear into every Croc hunter around, are now blue to me, but it is still not advisable to stand toe to toe with them. They provide pretty good XP (better than HG's in Rathe) although their loot leaves a bit to be desired, considering how tough they are. But, be that as it may, I have now developed a pretty good plan that works well.<br><br>The hardest part is pulling only one. One on one they pose little real threat. I routinely get two or more. I got 4 at once last night because I pulled the wrong spectre to start with.  Best to pull the ones on the West End of the island first.  This is also the closest point to the island.  There is usually one standing on the very corner.  I usually only get two when I pull here.  My plan has been to swim across the water to the island, climb up the steep bank till the Spectre is just barely in view. If he doesn’t aggro, I start with an Expulse spell so I’m doing damage right off the bat.  Then I BACK down the island bank (if you turn and run forward, you fall and take damage) get in the water and swim to shore.  My swimming skill is high so I leave them in the dust. <br><br>Once on shore, I turn and face the two chasing me whom are still in the water at this point. I root the one farthest away and prepare to SPOOK the one closest to me. I usually get a lfietap about this time for 34-37 pts and usually get whacked a time or two.  They can hit into the 90's.  I hit him with a SPOOK and her turns and runs along the shoreline. If my root holds for any length of time, I’m in good shape.  I follow along behind hacking and slashing.  After about 4-5 attacks, I SPOOK again, or if he turns on me sooner, I SPOOK, of course. I simply repeat this procedure until he is dead…keeping a wary eye for the one I left behind rooted.  If all goes well with no resists, I hardly even get hit and SPOOK takes very little mana! If the one I’ve rooted shows up, I simply SPPOK him to send him running, then reroot him.  <br><br>I have tried keeping two SPOOKED and it just didn’t work too well. Rooting one and SPOOKING one is the best way to go from what I’ve seen.  I’ve also tried nuking them to the ground with my Expulse Spell, but usually don’t have enough mana for that. Better to just follow along and hack. When the first one is dead, go find the other one.<br><br>If my druid friend is with me, it gets even easier.  Levitate across the water, Expulse to pull, have him snare the back one then root it,  I expulse the closest one again before it can get to me, then SPOOK it, while he DOT’s it.  After I’ve put some distance between me and the rooted one, chasing the one that’s SPOOKED, he snares the one I’m on and I can keep him continually SPOOKED at that point.  Hit 4-5 times, SPOOK, hit 4-5 times, SPOOK. He is dead in short order.  Repeat!<br><br>It takes a little effort and a little coordination, but so far it’s pretty fun! I should have tried it sooner, may around lvl 40-42. Thanks to the Paladin who motivated me to give this a try in the first place! Yet another place to Solo as a higher level Paladin! WOOT!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>46th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br><br>“Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness”<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
